  "name": "mariadb_bigquery_oracle_rows",
  "notes": "Hybrid of MariaDB (hash comments, NVL/IFNULL aliases, LIMIT syntax), BigQuery (case-preserving identifiers, strict booleans, GROUP BY alias resolution), and Oracle (MINUS for EXCEPT, EXTRACT temporal, NVL, SYSDATE). Unique axis is rows_unbounded_to_unbounded window frame default. FETCH as select keyword and FILTER as where keyword plus PARTITION BY for GROUP BY create a visually distinctive surface.",
